    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-05T17:09:46+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-05T17:09:46+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-05T07:39:46Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-05T07:39:46Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A trough over western WA linking to a weak front south of the Bight will continue to move over western and southern parts of SA later Sunday into Monday. A high pressure will move south of the Bight early in the week, before another trough and upper level system develops in the west. and moves across mid to late in the week, with a vigorous cold front to follow later Thursday and into Friday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW011" description="Eastern Eyre Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-05T15:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-05T05:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers, becoming less likely later tonight. The chance of a thunderstorm. Winds north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-06T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-05T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower. Winds north to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h shifting west to southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h in the middle of the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 17 with daytime temperatures reaching 28 to 33.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:20am to 3:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the afternoon and evening. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h increasing to 25 km/h before turning east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon and evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 16 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the morning. Light winds becoming north to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the morning then tending north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 14 with daytime temperatures reaching the high 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers. The chance of a thunderstorm in the morning and afternoon. Winds northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h turning west to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 15 and 18 with daytime temperatures reaching 25 to 31.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
